
[1]physic

   PHYS'IC, n. s as z. [Gr. from nature; to produce.]

   1. The art of healing diseases. This is now generally called medicine.

   2. Medicines; remedies for diseases. We desire physic only for the sake
   of health.

   3. In popular language, a medicine that purges; a purge; a cathartic.
   [In technical and elegant language this sense is not used.]

      PHYS'IC, v.t. To treat with physic; to evacuate the bowels with a
                            cathartic; to purge.

   1. To cure.
